-- 
Warsaw Shortlists Three for SPEC Sale, Rzeczpospolita Reports

-- B y   K a t y a   A n d r u s z
-- 
2011-06-11T09:37:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-11/warsaw-shortlists-three-for-spec-sale-rzeczpospolita-reports.html
The city of Warsaw has shortlisted
three companies to compete for the purchase of SPEC SA and may
complete the sale of the operator of the European Union’s
largest municipal heating network this month, daily
 Rzeczpospolita  reported.  Dalkia SA, Penta Investments Ltd. and Kulczyk Investments
SA are the shortlisted companies, Rzeczpospolita said. A joint
bid by PGE SA, Poland’s largest utility, and gas company  Polskie
Gornictwo Naftowe i Gazownictwo SA (PGN)  is out of the running,
Rzeczpospolita said, without saying where it got the
information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katya Andrusz at 
 kandrusz@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  